Exercise 1

pokemon <- pokemon %>% 
  clean_names()

pokem <- pokemon %>%
  filter(type_1 %in% c("Bug", "Fire", "Grass", "Normal", "Water", "Psychic"))

pokem$type_1 <- factor(pokem$type_1)
pokem$legendary <- factor(pokem$legendary)

set.seed(101)

pokem_split <- initial_split(pokem, prop = 0.80,
                          strata = type_1)
pokem_train <- training(pokem_split)
pokem_test <- testing(pokem_split)

dim(pokem_train)
## [1] 364  13
dim(pokem_test)
## [1] 94 13
pokem_folds <- vfold_cv(pokem_train, v = 5, strata = type_1)
pokem_folds
## #  5-fold cross-validation using stratification 
## # A tibble: 5 x 2
##   splits           id   
##   <list>           <chr>
## 1 <split [289/75]> Fold1
## 2 <split [291/73]> Fold2
## 3 <split [291/73]> Fold3
## 4 <split [292/72]> Fold4
## 5 <split [293/71]> Fold5
pokem_recipe <- recipe(type_1 ~ legendary + generation + sp_atk + attack + speed + defense + hp + sp_def,
                    data = pokem_train) %>%
  step_dummy(c(legendary, generation)) %>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors())

head(pokemon)

Exercise 3

tree_spec <- decision_tree() %>%
  set_engine("rpart")

class_tree_spec <- tree_spec %>%
  set_mode("classification")

class_tree_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(class_tree_spec %>% set_args(cost_complexity = tune())) %>%
  add_recipe(pokem_recipe)

param_grid <- grid_regular(cost_complexity(range = c(-3, -1)), levels = 10)

tune_res <- tune_grid(
  class_tree_wf,
  resamples = pokem_folds,
  grid = param_grid,
  metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
)

class_forest_spec <- rand_forest() %>%
  set_engine("ranger", importance = "impurity") %>%
  set_mode("classification")

param_grid2 <- grid_regular(mtry(range = c(1, 8)), trees(range = c(1,8)), min_n(range = c(1,8)),  levels = 8)

forest_workflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(class_forest_spec %>% set_args(mtry = tune(), trees = tune(), min_n = tune())) %>%
  add_recipe(pokem_recipe)
  1. mtry shouldn’t be smaller than 1 or larger than 8. Explain why not mtry should fall between 1 and 8 because there are 8 variables, hence, the maximum for mtry is 8.
  2. What type of model would mtry=8 represent? mtry=8 represents the creation of decision tree It should not be smaller than 1 or larger than 8 because the value does not show up correctly

Exercise 9

boost_spec <- boost_tree(trees = c(10,2000), tree_depth = 4) %>%
  set_engine("xgboost") %>%
  set_mode("classification")

param_grid_boost <- grid_regular(trees(range = c(10, 2000)),  levels = 10)

boost_workflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(boost_spec %>% set_args(trees = tune())) %>%
  add_recipe(pokem_recipe)

tune_res_boost <- tune_grid(
  boost_workflow,
  resamples = pokem_folds,
  grid = param_grid_boost,
  metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
